#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Allows you to access another computer's files using the <emphasis>S</"
"emphasis>ecure <emphasis>SH</emphasis>ell (<acronym>SSH</acronym>) protocol. "
"The remote computer needs to be running the <acronym>SSH</acronym> daemon, "
"but the remainder of the protocol uses standard commandline tools as "
"discussed below."
msgstr ""
"Permítelle acceder aos ficheiros que haxa noutro computador mediante o "
"protocolo S<emphasis>ecure</emphasis> SH<emphasis>ell</emphasis> "
"(<acronym>SSH</acronym>). O computador remoto precisa ter o servizo de "
"<acronym>SSH</acronym> en execución, pero o resto do protocolo usa "
"ferramentas estándar da liña de ordes como se explica a continuación."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use the fish KIO worker like this: <userinput>fish://"
"<replaceable>hostname</replaceable></userinput> or <userinput>fish://"
"<replaceable>username</replaceable>@<replaceable>hostname</replaceable></"
"userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Pode usar o traballador de KIO de fish así: <userinput>fish://"
"<replaceable>servidor</replaceable></userinput> ou <userinput>fish://"
"<replaceable>nome_de_usuario</replaceable>@<replaceable>servidor</"
"replaceable></userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "You need to use double forward slashes."
msgstr "Debe usar dúas barras."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:29
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can omit the <replaceable>username</replaceable> (and the trailing @ "
"symbol) if you have the same username on both computers."
msgstr ""
"Pode omitir a persoa <replaceable>usuaria</replaceable> (e o @ que lle "
"segue) se ten o mesmo nome de persoa usuaria nos dous computadores."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can add a password in the format: <userinput>fish://"
"<replaceable>username</replaceable>:<replaceable>password</"
"replaceable>@<replaceable>hostname</replaceable></userinput> but it is not "
"necessary as you will be prompted for one if it is not supplied."
msgstr ""
"Pode engadir un contrasinal co seguinte formato: <userinput>fish://"
"<replaceable>nome_de_usuario</replaceable>:<replaceable>contrasinal</"
"replaceable>@<replaceable>servidor</replaceable></userinput> pero non é "
"preciso xa que se lle preguntará se non o indicou."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:37
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are running the <acronym>SSH</acronym> daemon on a non-standard port, "
"you can specify that port using the normal &URL; syntax as shown below: "
"<userinput>fish://<replaceable>hostname</replaceable>:"
"<replaceable>portnumber</replaceable></userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Se está a executar o servizo de <acronym>SSH</acronym> nun porto non "
"estándar, pode indicar cal é usando a sintaxe normal dos &URL; deste xeito: "
"<userinput>fish://<replaceable>servidor</replaceable>:<replaceable>porto</"
"replaceable></userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:42
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Fish should work with any roughly <acronym>POSIX</acronym> compatible &UNIX; "
"based remote computer. It uses the shell commands <command>cat</command>, "
"<command>chgrp</command>, <command>chmod</command>, <command>chown</"
"command>, <command>cp</command>, <command>dd</command>, <command>env</"
"command>, <command>expr</command>, <command>grep</command>, <command>ls</"
"command>, <command>mkdir</command>, <command>mv</command>, <command>rm</"
"command>, <command>rmdir</command>, <command>sed</command>, and <command>wc</"
"command>. Fish starts <command>/bin/sh</command> as its shell and expects it "
"to be a Bourne shell (or compatible, like <command>bash</command>). If the "
"<command>sed</command> and <command>file</command> commands are available, "
"as well as a <filename>/etc/apache/magic</filename> file with &MIME; type "
"signatures, these will be used to guess &MIME; types."
msgstr ""
"Fish debe traballar con calquera computador remoto baseado en &UNIX; e que "
"sexa máis ou menos compatíbel con <acronym>POSIX</acronym>. Usa as ordes de "
"intérprete de ordes <command>cat</command>, <command>chgrp</command>, "
"<command>chmod</command>, <command>chown</command>, <command>cp</command>, "
"<command>dd</command>, <command>env</command>, <command>expr</command>, "
"<command>grep</command>, <command>ls</command>, <command>mkdir</command>, "
"<command>mv</command>, <command>rm</command>, <command>rmdir</command>, "
"<command>sed</command> e <command>wc</command>. Fish inicia <command>/bin/"
"sh</command> como intérprete de ordes e agarda que sexa un intérprete de "
"ordes Bourne (ou compatíbel, como <command>bash</command>). Se as ordes "
"<command>sed</command> e <command>file</command> están dispoñíbeis, así como "
"o ficheiro <filename>/etc/apache/magic</filename> con sinaturas de tipos "
"&MIME;, usaranse para adiviñar os tipos &MIME;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:61
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If <application>Perl</application> is available on the remote machine, it "
"will be used instead. Then only <command>env</command> and <command>/bin/sh</"
"command> are needed. Using <application>Perl</application> has the "
"additional benefit of being faster."
msgstr ""
"Se está dispoñíbel <application>Perl</application> na máquina remota, pode "
"usarse no canto. Entón só precisa <command>env</command> e <command>/bin/sh</"
"command>. Usar <application>Perl</application> ten a vantaxe adicional de "
"que é máis rápido."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Fish may even work on &Windows; machines, if tools like <application>Cygwin</"
"application> are installed. All the above utilities must be in the system "
"<envar>PATH</envar>, and the initial shell must be able to process the "
"command <command>echo FISH:;/bin/sh</command> correctly."
msgstr ""
"Fish pode mesmo traballar con máquinas &Windows;, se teñen instaladas "
"ferramentas como <application>Cygwin</application>. Todas as ferramentas "
"indicadas en riba deben estar na <envar>PATH</envar> do sistema, e o "
"intérprete de ordes inicial debe poder procesar a orde <command>echo FISH:;/"
"bin/sh</command> correctamente."
